HEADWORD: Semicubical
<hw>Sem`i*cu"bic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Math.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the square root of the cube of a
quantity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Semicubical parabola</b></col>, <cd>a curve in which the
ordinates are proportional to the square roots of the cubes of the
abscissas.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semicupium</ent>⟦br⟧
